.TH MRT_REPLY 2 "November 01, 2005"
.UC 5
.SH NAME
mrt_reply \- sends a message to a process through a MQ in an asynchronous manner 
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.ft B
#include <unistd.h>

int mrt_reply(mrtpid_t \fImrtpid\fP, Imrt_msg_t \fI*m_ptr\fP);
.ft R
.fi
.SH ARGUMENTS
.TP
.I \mrtpid
The RT-PID of the destination RT-process 
.TP
.I \m_ptr
A pointer to the message buffer 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B mrt_reply
sends a message to a process through a MQ in an asynchronous manner
.PP
It must be executed by a RT-process.
.SH "RETURN VALUE
Upon successful completion, a value of 0 (OK) is returned.  Otherwise,
a negative value is returned to indicate an error.
.SH ERRORS
.B mrt_reply
will fail if one or more of the following are true:
.TP 15
[E_MRT_NORTMODE]
The system is in Non Real Time processing Mode
.TP 15
[E_MRT_BADPTYPE]
The Source process is not a RT-process
.TP 15
[E_MRT_BADPTYPE]
The Destination process is not a RT-process
.TP 15
[E_BAD_DEST]
The Destination process is does not exist
.TP 15
[E_TRY_AGAIN]
The Destination process message queue is full
.TP 15
[E_MRT_NOMQENT]
The system message queue entry free pool is empty
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR mrt_arqst(2).
.BR mrt_uprqst(2).
